1
00:01:29,320 --> 00:01:32,000
=Our Days=

2
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:34,720
(Adapted from Lang Lang's original novel
"The Prime of the Goddess")

3
00:01:35,200 --> 00:01:38,160
=Episode 16=

4
00:01:38,375 --> 00:01:39,175
Who are you looking for?

5
00:01:41,136 --> 00:01:42,455
Is Wang Yuxi here?

6
00:01:43,255 --> 00:01:43,856
Dear,

7
00:01:44,056 --> 00:01:44,856
someone's looking for Yuxi.

8
00:01:45,255 --> 00:01:45,975
Who is it?

9
00:01:47,416 --> 00:01:48,375
Hello, you are...?

10
00:01:48,535 --> 00:01:49,815
I am Wang Yuxi's friend.

11
00:01:51,496 --> 00:01:52,535
He went back to Shanghai.

12
00:01:56,496 --> 00:01:57,535
When did he leave?

13
00:01:57,895 --> 00:01:58,975
It's been a few days.

14
00:02:01,455 --> 00:02:02,656
Sorry for the intrusion.

15
00:02:02,815 --> 00:02:03,416
Thanks.

16
00:02:03,455 --> 00:02:04,016
No problem.

17
00:02:17,296 --> 00:02:18,016
Sorry.

18
00:02:18,136 --> 00:02:19,136
The number you have dialed

19
00:02:19,175 --> 00:02:20,376
cannot be reached.

20
00:02:20,615 --> 00:02:21,775
Please try again later.

21
00:02:28,055 --> 00:02:29,416
I'm giving myself one month.

22
00:02:30,096 --> 00:02:31,096
I might go back to Shanghai

23
00:02:31,615 --> 00:02:32,935
or go somewhere else.

24
00:02:33,536 --> 00:02:34,495
The point is,

25
00:02:36,016 --> 00:02:37,016
I don't know whom I'm going to meet,

26
00:02:37,096 --> 00:02:38,016
or what kind.

27
00:02:39,256 --> 00:02:40,976
(The person you meet)

28
00:02:41,696 --> 00:02:43,376
(is going to decide where you go?)

29
00:02:43,935 --> 00:02:44,735
(Most likely.)

30
00:02:46,696 --> 00:02:48,136
(Just like what you like.)

31
00:02:48,696 --> 00:02:49,335
(There's no need)

32
00:02:49,335 --> 00:02:50,735
(to be concerned
with what others think.)

33
00:02:53,976 --> 00:02:55,256
(Xiang Zhong: Why aren't you replying?)

34
00:02:55,976 --> 00:02:57,096
(I know you went back to Shanghai.)

35
00:02:58,055 --> 00:02:59,136
(I want to talk to you face to face.)

36
00:03:10,696 --> 00:03:11,495
Eat up.

37
00:03:12,416 --> 00:03:13,775
Do you want the prawns?

38
00:03:15,735 --> 00:03:16,416
No thanks.

39
00:03:16,935 --> 00:03:17,856
Have the veges then.

40
00:03:19,495 --> 00:03:20,096
Aunty.

41
00:03:21,416 --> 00:03:22,735
Come and eat first.

42
00:03:22,895 --> 00:03:23,536
Coming.

43
00:03:24,696 --> 00:03:25,655
Coming.

44
00:03:26,935 --> 00:03:28,536
I learned a new recipe today.

45
00:03:28,856 --> 00:03:30,136
Try it and tell me how it is.

46
00:03:32,576 --> 00:03:34,175
What's the filling in the mushroom?

47
00:03:34,256 --> 00:03:35,536
I know you don't like meat.

48
00:03:35,735 --> 00:03:36,376
So I used shrimp

49
00:03:36,376 --> 00:03:37,696
for the filling.

50
00:03:37,856 --> 00:03:38,376
Do you like it?

51
00:03:38,376 --> 00:03:39,175
It's really good.

52
00:03:39,376 --> 00:03:39,935
Is it?

53
00:03:39,935 --> 00:03:40,696
I want one too.

54
00:03:40,696 --> 00:03:41,775
- Here you go.
- It's good.

55
00:03:41,816 --> 00:03:42,856
I want one too.

56
00:03:42,856 --> 00:03:43,376
It's good?

57
00:03:43,696 --> 00:03:44,416
There's more.

58
00:03:44,655 --> 00:03:45,615
But I haven't steamed them.

59
00:03:45,775 --> 00:03:46,696
Let me go do it now.

60
00:03:46,895 --> 00:03:47,856
Don't worry about it, Aunty.

61
00:03:47,895 --> 00:03:48,495
I'll be quick.

62
00:03:48,615 --> 00:03:50,096
Do it and come back to eat, okay?

63
00:03:50,296 --> 00:03:50,895
Grandaunt,

64
00:03:50,895 --> 00:03:52,296
it's so delicious.

65
00:03:52,296 --> 00:03:53,696
I really like it.

66
00:03:53,895 --> 00:03:55,296
It's really good, right?

67
00:03:55,296 --> 00:03:55,976
Is it?

68
00:03:56,136 --> 00:03:56,816
Yes.

69
00:03:56,856 --> 00:03:58,175
We'll ask grandaunt to make more.

70
00:04:00,055 --> 00:04:01,296
Your relationship suddenly improved.

71
00:04:01,856 --> 00:04:03,136
It's the power of communication.

72
00:04:09,536 --> 00:04:10,376
Prof. Yang assigned me

73
00:04:10,416 --> 00:04:11,696
two more new projects.

74
00:04:11,935 --> 00:04:13,016
I haven't joined the postdoctoral program

75
00:04:13,735 --> 00:04:14,615
but I'm already exhausted.

76
00:04:14,856 --> 00:04:15,895
I see it now.

77
00:04:15,935 --> 00:04:16,775
The role of a post-doc

78
00:04:16,775 --> 00:04:17,855
is just cheap labor.

79
00:04:19,376 --> 00:04:20,295
It's not that bad.

80
00:04:20,376 --> 00:04:21,736
Being busy is a good thing.

81
00:04:22,256 --> 00:04:23,816
Don't complain, be content.

82
00:04:23,855 --> 00:04:25,295
I'm not complaining.

83
00:04:26,256 --> 00:04:27,736
I was thinking,

84
00:04:27,816 --> 00:04:28,455
since Cong and Qi

85
00:04:28,455 --> 00:04:29,895
are starting primary school soon,

86
00:04:30,295 --> 00:04:31,215
I could handle

87
00:04:31,415 --> 00:04:32,376
their pre-school tutoring myself.

88
00:04:32,655 --> 00:04:33,496
But,

89
00:04:33,855 --> 00:04:34,616
now it looks like

90
00:04:34,696 --> 00:04:35,335
I won't have

91
00:04:35,376 --> 00:04:36,655
a lot of free time moving forward.

92
00:04:38,535 --> 00:04:39,895
Having a post-doc student

93
00:04:40,415 --> 00:04:41,176
to tutor

94
00:04:41,176 --> 00:04:42,576
two pre-school children,

95
00:04:43,215 --> 00:04:44,616
isn't that a waste of talent?

96
00:04:46,696 --> 00:04:47,295
It's okay.

97
00:04:47,376 --> 00:04:49,176
I'll find an agency

98
00:04:49,855 --> 00:04:51,176
to help look for a private tutor.

99
00:04:52,816 --> 00:04:53,576
Actually,

100
00:04:53,576 --> 00:04:54,736
there's no need for that.

101
00:04:55,176 --> 00:04:56,176
No, don't touch that.

102
00:04:56,215 --> 00:04:57,136
I'm putting them in groups.

103
00:04:58,936 --> 00:05:00,136
This is what I'm thinking.

104
00:05:02,295 --> 00:05:04,056
Instead of hiring a tutor outside,

105
00:05:04,056 --> 00:05:05,696
why don't I head to the research center
and see if

106
00:05:05,775 --> 00:05:06,696
there are any juniors willing
to do part-time work

107
00:05:06,775 --> 00:05:08,256
to support their studies?

108
00:05:09,095 --> 00:05:10,176
Firstly,

109
00:05:10,256 --> 00:05:11,576
I know them better.

110
00:05:12,095 --> 00:05:13,176
Secondly,

111
00:05:13,616 --> 00:05:14,696
it's cheaper than hiring
a private tutor.

112
00:05:14,895 --> 00:05:15,975
We can save some money too.

113
00:05:16,056 --> 00:05:17,016
What do you think?

114
00:05:18,696 --> 00:05:19,816
What did you say just now?

115
00:05:20,376 --> 00:05:21,176
Something about labor.

116
00:05:21,256 --> 00:05:22,775
Cheap labor, wasn't it?

117
00:05:23,655 --> 00:05:25,095
You sure picked it up quickly.

118
00:05:26,855 --> 00:05:28,415
Well, the apple doesn't fall
far away from the tree.

119
00:05:30,016 --> 00:05:31,295
Are there any kids

120
00:05:31,535 --> 00:05:32,816
younger than Cong and Qi

121
00:05:33,415 --> 00:05:34,616
in your hometown?

122
00:05:35,176 --> 00:05:35,775
Clothes

123
00:05:35,775 --> 00:05:36,895
that our kids no longer wear...

124
00:05:37,295 --> 00:05:38,535
I mean, which they've outgrown,

125
00:05:38,616 --> 00:05:39,855
are still in good condition.

126
00:05:40,535 --> 00:05:42,215
We can send them back.

127
00:05:43,535 --> 00:05:44,616
I'll ask around.

128
00:05:46,136 --> 00:05:47,016
I take it that you're okay

129
00:05:47,016 --> 00:05:48,056
about my looking for a tutor.

130
00:05:58,415 --> 00:05:59,496
Here, come in.

131
00:06:01,936 --> 00:06:02,736
You can wear these.

132
00:06:02,736 --> 00:06:03,855
Okay, thanks, Gao Ping.

133
00:06:03,895 --> 00:06:04,576
Xiang Qian.

134
00:06:05,535 --> 00:06:06,256
Xiang Qian.

135
00:06:07,975 --> 00:06:08,775
The tutor is here.

136
00:06:08,855 --> 00:06:09,816
Come and meet her.

137
00:06:15,136 --> 00:06:15,895
Hello, Mrs. Gao.

138
00:06:16,016 --> 00:06:16,496
Hello.

139
00:06:16,576 --> 00:06:17,256
This is Li Shu,

140
00:06:17,455 --> 00:06:18,335
one of our research students.

141
00:06:18,415 --> 00:06:19,016
She does

142
00:06:19,016 --> 00:06:19,936
most of the administrative work.

143
00:06:20,455 --> 00:06:21,095
Nice to meet you.

144
00:06:21,256 --> 00:06:22,176
Come, take a seat.

145
00:06:22,616 --> 00:06:23,696
Go sit, I'll get water.

146
00:06:23,895 --> 00:06:24,455
Sit.

147
00:06:28,975 --> 00:06:30,016
- Here, water.
- Thanks.

148
00:06:30,655 --> 00:06:31,616
Water for you.

149
00:06:31,655 --> 00:06:32,335
Thanks.

150
00:06:33,895 --> 00:06:35,415
What a pretty glass.

151
00:06:35,895 --> 00:06:37,295
My younger sister made it.

152
00:06:40,056 --> 00:06:40,535
Mrs. Gao,

153
00:06:40,696 --> 00:06:41,936
before coming here,

154
00:06:42,016 --> 00:06:43,576
I did a lot of research.

155
00:06:43,895 --> 00:06:45,936
I believe that
for pre-school-aged children,

156
00:06:45,975 --> 00:06:46,775
the most important thing

157
00:06:46,816 --> 00:06:47,736
is to be happy.

158
00:06:48,176 --> 00:06:49,535
So my idea is

159
00:06:49,616 --> 00:06:51,455
to conduct handicraft lessons

160
00:06:51,816 --> 00:06:53,576
to nurture their ability to focus

161
00:06:53,655 --> 00:06:54,455
and concentrate.

162
00:06:54,895 --> 00:06:55,855
Personally,

163
00:06:55,975 --> 00:06:57,095
my hobby is clay baking.

164
00:06:57,256 --> 00:06:58,056
I think

165
00:06:58,095 --> 00:06:59,136
I can do that with the kids.

166
00:07:00,095 --> 00:07:00,936
As for study materials,

167
00:07:01,095 --> 00:07:01,895
I prepared these.

168
00:07:02,655 --> 00:07:03,816
You can take a look.

169
00:07:05,056 --> 00:07:05,736
First of all,

170
00:07:05,736 --> 00:07:07,016
there are some

171
00:07:07,295 --> 00:07:09,095
easy pinyin lessons.

172
00:07:10,256 --> 00:07:11,696
For math, there's addition

173
00:07:11,855 --> 00:07:13,295
and subtraction within 10

174
00:07:13,335 --> 00:07:14,136
and applied problems.

175
00:07:15,095 --> 00:07:15,975
For English,

176
00:07:16,136 --> 00:07:17,256
I prepared

177
00:07:17,335 --> 00:07:18,415
some fables.

178
00:07:19,855 --> 00:07:20,775
Also,

179
00:07:21,376 --> 00:07:22,616
for reading, I have

180
00:07:22,696 --> 00:07:23,655
the Nineteen Ancient Poems,

181
00:07:23,696 --> 00:07:24,975
and some introductory

182
00:07:25,056 --> 00:07:26,295
Song and Tang poems.

183
00:07:27,535 --> 00:07:28,616
Because I think

184
00:07:28,616 --> 00:07:29,616
for pre-school children,

185
00:07:29,775 --> 00:07:31,376
the learning content

186
00:07:31,455 --> 00:07:32,335
isn't that important.

187
00:07:32,655 --> 00:07:34,095
What matters is

188
00:07:34,295 --> 00:07:35,816
stimulating an interest in learning.

189
00:07:36,576 --> 00:07:38,016
So the materials I have

190
00:07:38,016 --> 00:07:39,176
aren't that complicated.

191
00:07:39,256 --> 00:07:40,616
Is there anything particular you need,

192
00:07:40,655 --> 00:07:41,616
Mr. and Mrs. Gao?

193
00:07:45,576 --> 00:07:46,616
I think it's quite good.

194
00:07:46,975 --> 00:07:48,655
Let's go ahead and give it a try.

195
00:07:49,295 --> 00:07:50,215
Okay.

196
00:07:53,616 --> 00:07:54,975
We are back.

197
00:07:55,415 --> 00:07:56,696
You're back, my babies?

198
00:07:59,295 --> 00:08:00,176
Come, Cong and Qi.

199
00:08:00,176 --> 00:08:00,736
Come here.

200
00:08:01,616 --> 00:08:02,696
Greet Ms. Li.

201
00:08:03,056 --> 00:08:04,736
Hello, Ms. Li.

202
00:08:04,775 --> 00:08:06,295
Hello, Qi and Cong.

203
00:08:06,455 --> 00:08:07,376
I brought

204
00:08:07,535 --> 00:08:09,136
some gifts for you two.

205
00:08:09,415 --> 00:08:11,576
This little boy is for Cong.

206
00:08:11,696 --> 00:08:13,215
Thank you, Ms. Li.

207
00:08:13,376 --> 00:08:14,616
The little girl is for Qi.

208
00:08:14,816 --> 00:08:16,655
Thanks, Ms. Li.

209
00:08:16,936 --> 00:08:17,895
Do you like it?

210
00:08:18,016 --> 00:08:18,936
Yes.

211
00:08:19,176 --> 00:08:20,496
Let's make some handicrafts

212
00:08:20,616 --> 00:08:21,696
together next time, okay?

213
00:08:21,855 --> 00:08:23,016
Okay.

214
00:08:24,616 --> 00:08:25,136
Xiang Qian.

215
00:08:25,576 --> 00:08:26,215
Ms. Li

216
00:08:26,215 --> 00:08:27,295
will be eating dinner with us, right?

217
00:08:27,535 --> 00:08:28,415
I'll prepare more.

218
00:08:28,535 --> 00:08:29,616
It's okay, Aunty.

219
00:08:29,736 --> 00:08:31,256
I have an English class later.

220
00:08:33,016 --> 00:08:33,976
I briefly told her

221
00:08:34,055 --> 00:08:35,216
about our family condition.

222
00:08:38,415 --> 00:08:39,935
You're still attending classes?

223
00:08:41,096 --> 00:08:42,415
Are you preparing to go abroad?

224
00:08:43,575 --> 00:08:44,295
Cong.

225
00:08:44,535 --> 00:08:46,055
I'm thinking,

226
00:08:46,655 --> 00:08:47,976
since the current job market is...

227
00:08:48,256 --> 00:08:49,295
Go and wash your hands.

228
00:08:49,695 --> 00:08:51,096
Go wash your hands.

229
00:08:53,136 --> 00:08:54,575
I'm thinking

230
00:08:55,016 --> 00:08:57,175
I should give myself more options.

231
00:08:57,496 --> 00:08:58,456
Because currently,

232
00:08:58,456 --> 00:08:59,856
the local job market is not promising.

233
00:09:00,295 --> 00:09:02,096
Gao Ping should know that too, right?

234
00:09:02,895 --> 00:09:05,016
Don't you guys have any plans
to go abroad?

235
00:09:06,295 --> 00:09:07,775
No, we're not thinking of that.

236
00:09:08,256 --> 00:09:09,695
When Cong and Qi are older,

237
00:09:09,775 --> 00:09:10,856
they can decide for themselves.

238
00:09:11,216 --> 00:09:12,376
Yeah, we are
a multi-generational family.

239
00:09:12,456 --> 00:09:13,575
It's not that easy to move.

240
00:09:16,575 --> 00:09:17,216
Got it.

241
00:09:17,695 --> 00:09:18,496
Okay, Mrs. Gao.

242
00:09:18,655 --> 00:09:19,456
I'll get going.

243
00:09:19,575 --> 00:09:20,895
I'll take these with me first.

244
00:09:21,055 --> 00:09:21,736
I'll bring them again

245
00:09:21,935 --> 00:09:22,736
the next time I come.

246
00:09:22,976 --> 00:09:23,336
Okay.

247
00:09:23,496 --> 00:09:24,216
Thank you.

248
00:09:25,216 --> 00:09:26,096
Oh, Gao Ping.

249
00:09:26,575 --> 00:09:28,016
Is it easy to get a taxi here?

250
00:09:28,456 --> 00:09:29,055
Yeah, I think so.

251
00:09:29,535 --> 00:09:30,336
Where are you headed?

252
00:09:31,256 --> 00:09:32,295
To the subway station.

253
00:09:33,815 --> 00:09:35,216
You can drive her, Gao Ping.

254
00:09:36,935 --> 00:09:37,736
No, it's okay. Mrs. Gao.

255
00:09:37,976 --> 00:09:38,695
I don't want to trouble you.

256
00:09:38,856 --> 00:09:39,496
I can find a way.

257
00:09:39,575 --> 00:09:40,815
No, the subway station

258
00:09:40,856 --> 00:09:41,856
is a distance away from here.

259
00:09:42,256 --> 00:09:43,415
Better to take her, Gao Ping.

260
00:09:44,496 --> 00:09:45,736
Okay, I'll drive you. Let's go.

261
00:09:46,935 --> 00:09:47,376
Okay.

262
00:09:47,376 --> 00:09:48,175
I'll be off, Mrs. Gao.

263
00:09:48,295 --> 00:09:49,136
See you next time.

264
00:09:49,256 --> 00:09:49,736
See you.

265
00:09:49,895 --> 00:09:50,336
Bye-bye.

266
00:09:50,415 --> 00:09:50,935
Bye.

267
00:09:51,336 --> 00:09:52,136
Thanks for coming.

268
00:09:53,575 --> 00:09:54,295
I'll drive her.

269
00:09:56,895 --> 00:09:58,415
Bye, Cong and Qi.

270
00:09:58,695 --> 00:10:00,336
Bye-bye, Ms. Li.

271
00:10:00,616 --> 00:10:01,655
Aunty, see you.

272
00:10:08,256 --> 00:10:08,736
I look

273
00:10:08,895 --> 00:10:09,775
better without glasses, right?

274
00:10:10,736 --> 00:10:12,016
When did you get engaged?

275
00:10:13,895 --> 00:10:14,736
You mean this?

276
00:10:16,096 --> 00:10:17,535
I borrowed it from my housemate.

277
00:10:18,256 --> 00:10:19,216
I was thinking,

278
00:10:19,415 --> 00:10:20,856
if I look like I'm engaged,

279
00:10:21,096 --> 00:10:21,775
your wife would

280
00:10:21,976 --> 00:10:23,096
probably lower her guard a little.

281
00:10:24,055 --> 00:10:24,976
There's no need for that.

282
00:10:25,216 --> 00:10:26,295
Xiang Qian has quite a lot of trust

283
00:10:26,295 --> 00:10:27,336
in our relationship.

284
00:10:28,376 --> 00:10:29,336
Is that so?

285
00:10:30,016 --> 00:10:31,016
I don't buy it.

286
00:10:31,575 --> 00:10:32,616
You're a standout.

287
00:10:32,775 --> 00:10:34,175
How can she be so confident?

288
00:10:35,575 --> 00:10:36,655
Can I ask you

289
00:10:36,695 --> 00:10:38,016
not to make such cringey remarks?

290
00:10:38,496 --> 00:10:40,096
Which one? A standout?

